ASDA Holt Park Proposals – Have Your Say
- Alex Sobel
- Nov 13, 2018
- 1 min read
I recently received a letter from Asda regarding their proposals for the Adel Holt Park Store and Holt Park Centre. I would encourage any interested residents to have their views heard by taking part in the consultation, details of which can be found on their letter below:
Asda will shortly be submitting plans to Leeds City Council for significant investment proposals at our Adel Holt Park Store and the wider Holt Park Centre.
The proposals include:
An updated Asda store;
Car park improvements;
New toilets;
New customer entrance;
The provision of new retail outlets;
The provision of a café; and
The reconfiguration and upgrading of the public realm.
The proposals will be on full public display at The Holt Park Centre on Friday 23rd (12:00 – 18:00) and Saturday 24th (10:00 – 13:00) November. This display will also be staffed by members of the project team. A website with more details of the proposals will be live from 12:00 Thursday 22nd November at www.holtparkfeedback.com and will remain live until the application is submitted.
If you would like to know more about the exciting future we propose for Holt Park and Asda Adel, please contact our hotline on 0800 088 4322 or email Asdaconsultation@pagodapr.com
